<dl id="n06067c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06067c">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06067c"> 67(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> plank floor so that bed / can stand on it ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Entra&icirc;nement des enfants &agrave; la propret&eacute; et aux soins ponctuels. <i>A New-York</i>, <mark>le sol est planch&eacute;i&eacute;</mark> et non carrel&eacute; et la directrice m&apos;explique <mark>que c&apos;est &ldquo;afin que les enfants aient les pieds chauds</mark> et que ceux qui jouent &agrave; terre ne prennent point de rhumatismes pr&eacute;coces, ni d&apos;ent&eacute;rites par refroidissement&rdquo;. <font color="green">[Training of children in cleanliness and punctuality. In New York, the floor is plank and not tiled and the director explains that it is &ldquo;so that children have warm feet and those who play on the ground do not take any early rheumatism or enteritis by cooling&rdquo;.]</font> <small> ?. ?, <a name="LARA" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#LARA"><cite title="source">La Revue Philantropique</cite></a> (????) 228</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
